AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> "has process attribute"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> "has process attribute from OEO https://openenergyplatform.org/ontology/oeo/OEO_00000500"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> "A relation between a process and a process attribute that depends on it."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> "Tensile testing process has process attribute tensile rate"@en)
ObjectPropertyDomain(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)
ObjectPropertyRange(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069> (has state)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069> "has state"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069> "relates a temporally qualified continuant to the unique anchor continuant that it is a temporal phase of"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001032> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069> "https://github.com/materialdigital/core-ontology/issues/185")
InverseObjectProperties(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000070>)
InverseFunctionalObjectProperty(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069>)
ObjectPropertyDomain(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000002> ObjectComplementOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000068>)))
ObjectPropertyRange(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000069> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000068>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000070> (is state of)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000070> "is state of"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000070> "relates a temporally qualified continuant to the unique anchor continuant that it is a temporal phase of")
FunctionalObjectProperty(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000070>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> (specified by value)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> "specified by value"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> "A relation between an entity and a value specification which is about this entity."@en)
SubObjectPropertyOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000004>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001030> (stimulated by)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001030> "stimulated by"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001030> "inverse of stimulates"@en)
SubObjectPropertyOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001030> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054>)
ObjectPropertyRange(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001030> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020127> (refers to)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020127> "Despite has characteristic from RO does not have any domain constraints, it is still not possible to directly connect an instance of a process with an instance of a SDC. 

First, SDC is dependent on a IC. As RO does not have \"bearer of\" object property, the \"has characteristic\" implies that the domain should be an IC. 

Second, characteristic of is a functional property. Thus, two triples SDC_1 characteristc of IC_1 and SDC_2  characteristc of Process_1 (where IC_1 participates in Process_1), cannot exist simultaneously. 
An example of such case can be \"Temperature of during the annealing process was 1000°C\". Temperature is an SDC of some participant of the annealing, however it is not clear whether it is an SDC of an oven or of a sample in the oven. If we assert triple Annealing--> has characteristic --> Temperature 1000°C, then the correct triple connecting temperature SDC with either oven or specimen cannot exist."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020127> "refers to"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020127> "a relation between a process attribute and an SDC of some participant in a process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020127> "a relation to between a process attribute an a SDC of some participant in a process."@en)
ObjectPropertyDomain(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020127> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>)
ObjectPropertyRange(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020127> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000020>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> (has relational quality)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> "has relational quality"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> "a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a relational quality, in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> "material has relational quality mass proportion m, and portion of iron has the same relational quality mass proportion m"@en)
SubObjectPropertyOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> owl:topObjectProperty)
InverseObjectProperties(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999>)
ObjectPropertyRange(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000145>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> (relational quality of)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> "The 'relational quality of' is more strict that 'quality of' from RO, since domain is 'relational quality'. The motivtion to introduce an object property for relational qualities is the following:
RO's 'quality of' is functional i.e., a->b, a->c => b=c. The functionality is relevant for most of the SDC -> IC triples, expect for relational qualities, which per definiton can be simultaneously inherited in >=2 ICs. Thus,  'relational quality of'  has the same intention to connect SDC to IC, however, without cardinality constraints."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> "relational quality of"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> "a relation between a relational quality and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> "mass proportion m is relational qualitiy of material, and the same mass proportion m is relational qualitiy of portion of iron"@en)
SubObjectPropertyOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> owl:topObjectProperty)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066> (geometrically related)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066> "This object property is not intended to be used between intances."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066> "geometrically related"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066> "Geometrically related is a top-level object property to describe geometrical relations between different spatial regions"@en)
ObjectPropertyDomain(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000006>)
ObjectPropertyRange(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000006>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000067> (parallel to)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000067> "Parallel to is an object property which connect two or  more spatial regions that are parallel to each other"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000067> "parallel to"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000067> "<111> family of directions in crystals are parellel to normal direction (ND) of a sample in γ-fiber texture component"@en)
SubObjectPropertyOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000067> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066>)
SymmetricObjectProperty(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000067>)
TransitiveObjectProperty(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000067>)

# Object Property: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000068> (normal to)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000068> "normal to"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000068> "Normal to is a object property which describes geometric relation between two spatial regions which are normal to each other"@en)
SubObjectPropertyOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000068> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000066>)
SymmetricObjectProperty(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000068>)


