# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> (length)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "Length is a size that describes the spacial extend of its bearer in one dimension."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "length"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "dimension"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "Length is a one dimensional size.")
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> (bond)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> "bond"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> "A bond is a relational quality describing the force interaction between atoms."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020200>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> (metallic bond)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <https://www.thoughtco.com/metallic-bond-definition-properties-and-examples-4117948>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> "metallic bond"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> "A metallic bond is a bond that forms between metal atoms, where electrons are shared in a \"sea\" of electrons that move freely around the metal ions. This type of bonding gives metals their characteristic properties such as conductivity and malleability."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> (Durchmesser)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "“Diameter.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/diameter. Accessed 5 Dec. 2022.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "Durchmesser"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "diameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/2.0.8/Diameter>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "Die Länge einer geraden Linie durch den Mittelpunkt eines Objekts oder Raums."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "The length of a straight line through the center of an object or space."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> (thickness)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> "Dicke"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> "thickness"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/2.0.8/Thickness>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> "Diese Klasse beschreibt das gemessene Maß in einer Richtung eines Prüfkörpers."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> "This class describes the measured dimension in one direction of a test piece."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> (Breite)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> "Breite"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> "width"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/2.0.8/Width>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> <https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/width>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> "Diese Klasse beschreibt eine horizontale Messung eines Objekts, die im rechten Winkel zur Länge des Objekts vorgenommen wird."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> "This class describes a horizontal measurement of an object taken at right angles to the length of the object."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050154> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> (shape)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "“Shape.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/shape. Accessed 13 Jan. 2023.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "Form"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "shape"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "Das sichtbare Ausstattungsmerkmal (räumliche Form oder Kontur) eines bestimmten Objektes oder einer Art von Objekt."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "The visible makeup characteristic (spatial form or contour) of a particular item or kind of item.a"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> (Geometrische Form)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "DIN EN ISO 6892-1:2019")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "Geometrische Form"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "geometry shape"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "Dieses Konzept beschreibt die geometrischen Abmessungen und das Erscheinungsbild (Form und Abmaße) einer Probe, eines Prüfkörpers oder eines Prüfstücks, wie sie üblicherweise durch eine entsprechende Norm definiert sind. Dementsprechend ist der angegebene Formwert in Übereinstimmung mit der definierenden Norm anzugeben, z. B. \"Zugprüfstück Form 1 gemäß Anhang B der Zugversuchsnorm\"."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "This concept describes the geometric dimensions and appearance (shape and dimensions) of a sample, specimen, or test piece as usually defined by a corresponding standard. Accordingly, the shape value given is in accordance with the defining standard, e.g., ‘tensile test piece shape 1 in accordance with annex B of the tensile test standard’."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> (3D Geometrie)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "3D Geometrie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "shape 3d"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "A shape 3D is a geometry shape that exists in three dimensions, having length, width, and height, and can be defined by its spatial properties such as volume and surface area."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "Eine 3D Geometrie ist eine geometrische Form, die in drei Dimensionen existiert, mit Länge, Breite und Höhe, und die durch ihre räumlichen Eigenschaften wie Volumen und Oberfläche definiert werden kann."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "Beispiele sind Formen wie Würfel, Kugeln und Pyramiden."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "Examples include shapes like cubes, spheres, and pyramids."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000000> (crystallographic direction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000000> "TODO: refine the axiom to the object aggregates grains"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000000> "crystallographic direction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000000> "Crystallographic direction is a vector within a crystal unit cell, which passes through the origin of crystal reference frame and a specified point in the unit cell. Crystallographic direction is a part of crystal or grain."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000000> "[110] direction in a cubic unit cell, <110> family of directions in a cubic unit cell"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000000> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000026>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000000> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ObjectUnionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001> (rolled sheet direction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001> "TODO: add device to the exception"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001> "rolled sheet direction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001> "Rolled sheet direction is a one-dimensional spatial region which determines the directions in a sheet material in respect to the rolling direction. Rolled sheet direction is a part of material or object."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000026>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ObjectUnionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> ObjectComplementOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003>) ObjectComplementOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020113>)))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000002> (rolled sheet directions)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000002> "rolled sheet directions"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000002> "Rolled sheet directions is a categorical value specification which specifies the rolled sheet direction. It  includes rolling direction (RD), transverse direction (TD), and normal direction (ND)"@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000002> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000028> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000029> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000030>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000002> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001930>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> (magnetic field alternating frequency)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> "magnetic field alternating frequency"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> (plot)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> "plot"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> "A plot is a 2-D information content entity describing a dependency of one variable on another."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> "B-H curve, stress-strain curve"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000502>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> (B-H curve)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> "B-H curve"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> "B-H curve is a plot which describes the dependency of magnetic flux density B on magnetic field strength H in soft and hard magnetic materials."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> (stress-strain curve)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> "stress-strain curve"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> "Stress-strain curve is a plot which describes the dependency of deformation in a sample on the applied stress (force per unit area)."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> (3D)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> "3D"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> "A three-dimensional information content entity is a representation or analysis, commonly applied in studying material properties in its volume or describing a dependency of one variable on two other variables"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000030>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> (orientation distribution function)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> "orientation distribution function"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> "ODF"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> "Orientation distrubution function (ODF) is a 3D information content entity which quantitively describes texture (preferred crystallographic orientation of grains) in polycrystalline materials. ODF can be caclulated from pole figures obtained from the diffraction patterns."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> (EBSD map)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> "EBSD map"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> "EBSD (electron backscatter diffraction) map represents a information content entity which is determined analytically from data obtrained from EBSD characterization. EBSD map provides information about grain size and grain orientation."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> (quasi-static (DC) characterization of magnetic properties)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "TODO: The definition has to be refined. 
TODO: Write axioms based on the definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "quasi-static (DC) characterization of magnetic properties"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "Quasi-static (DC) characterization is a magnetic properties analyzing process for soft magnetic sheet materials which aims to determine a static magnetic curve of the tested material. During the test, the current in the primary winding is changed slowly, thus the frequency of a magnetic field remains low, i.e., below 0.01 Hz. The output of the quasi-static characterization of magnetic properties  is a static B-H curve, which  provides information on hysteresis loss Ph, saturation magnetization Bs, coercivity Hc, remanence Br, and maximum permeability µmax. During DC characterization primarily domain wall motion and pinning effects play role."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "Measurement of hysteresis losses; measurement of magnetic induction at specified magnetic field, e.g., 5000 A/m."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> (dynamic (AC) characterization of magnetic properties)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "Dynamic (AC) characterization of magnetic properties is a magnetic properties analyzing process for soft magnetic sheet materials which aims to determine the total energy loss of a tested material at specific frequency and magnetic flux density. During the test, the current in the primary winding is changed with frequency between 50-400 Hz to ensure sinusoidal waveform of the magnetic flux density at Bpeak. The output of the dynamic characterization of magnetic properties  is a  B-H curve, which  provides information on total core loss Ptot and dynamic permeability µdyn."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "TODO: refine defintion
TODO: write axioms"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "dynamic (AC) characterization of magnetic properties"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "Measurement of total power (iron) loss at given current frequency and maximal magnetic induction, e.g. 50 Hz and 1.5 T, or 400 Hz and 1.0 T"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> (magnetic property analyzing process using Epstein frame)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> "magnetic property analyzing process using Epstein frame"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> "Magnetic property analyzing process using Epstein frame is a standardized assay which uses Epstein frame to test magnetic properties of soft magnetic materials, where several (how many) strips are stacked."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> (magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> "magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> "magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester is an assay for determining magnetic properties of soft mangetic materials, where magnetic field H is applied to a single sheet."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> (magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> "magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> "Magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core is an assay for determing magnetic properties of soft magnetic materials, where the sample has closed wound ring core shape. As the ring shape does not have any air gaps or joint losses, this testing procedure provides information on most intrinsic material properties."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> (cold rolling)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> "Cold rolling is a rolling process which aims to reduce thickness of a metallic sheet. Cold rolling takes place at room temperature."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> "cold rolling"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> (hot rolling)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> "Hot rolling is a rolling process which aims to reduce the thickness of a sheet material. Hot rolling  takes place at temperatures above alloy's recrystallization temperature."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> "hot rolling"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> (naturally occuring process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> "naturally occuring process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> "Naturally occuring process is a process which occurs in materials due to external stimulus which is part of some planned process."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> (recrystallization)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> "follows  Arrhenius equation.
Has part grain growth and recovery."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> "recrystallization"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> "Recrystallization is a naturally occuring process which occurs in metallic materials and during which deformed grains are replaced by new defect-free grains. Recrystallization is a thermally activated process, i.e., it requires sufficiently high temperatures for the process to occur. Thus, recrystallization is a process which is part of annealing heat treatment."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> (recovery)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> "recovery"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> "Recovery is a naturally occuring process which occurs in metallic materials and during which the reduction of stored deformation energy in grains occurs due to the removal and rearragement of crystal structure defects (dislocations). Recovery is a part of recrystallization process, thus it is a thermally activated process, which occurs during annealing heat treatment."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> (grain growth)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> "grain growth"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> "Grain growth is a naturally occuring process which occurs in polycrystalline materials. The driving force of grain growth is reduction of the interal energy via reduction of the total grain boundary. Grain growth is a thermally activated process which occurs after recovery and (primary) recrystallization."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> (domain wall motion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> "domain wall motion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> "Domain wall motion is a naturally occuring process which occurs in ferromagnetic materials due to the external stimulus such as applied magnetic field."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> (domain wall pinning)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> "domain wall pinning"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> "Domain wall pinning is a naturally occuring process which occurs in ferromagnetic materials when domain wall montion is temporally inhibited due to an energy barrier."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> (rolling)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> "Rolling is a shaping process in which material is passed through under a roll with the goal of reducing the thickness of a semi-finished object. After rolling the mateiral deformed microstructure, which is characterized by elongated defomed grains, high dislocation density, high internal strains, and preferred grain orientation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> "rolling"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> (strip-casting)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> "The defintion has potential"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> "strip-casting"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> "Strip-casting is a primary shaping from fluid state process for metals and alloys. During Strip-casting the melt flows between two rolls resulting in the strip."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> (forging)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> "Schmieden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> "forging"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> "Forging is a pressure forming process of metals and alloys. During forging the material is heated to forging temperature and formed to the desired form using either hammers and anvils or heat-resistant upper and lower dies."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> (normalizing)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> "normalizing"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> "Normalizing is a heat treatment process which aims to create uniform grain structure and improve toughness of an alloy. During normalizing the material is heated above its critical temperature, kept at this temperature for a period of time, and then cooled in the air."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> (annealing)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> "annealing"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> "Annealing is a heat treatment process which aims to soften an alloy and relieve internal stresses. The material is heated above its critical termperature at which recrystallization occurs. After holding the material at the temperature, it is cooled in a slow and controlled way usually inside an oven."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> (noes characteristic texture components)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> "noes characteristic texture components"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> "NOES characteristic texture components are the texure components which most commonly found in non-oriented electrical sheets. These components form preferred grain orientations in NOES, characterized by family of planes {hkl} oriented parallel to the rolling plane (RP) and family of directions <uvw> oriented parallel to the rolling direction (RD)."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000035> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000036>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001930>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> (scanning electron microscopy)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "scanning electron microscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "https://www.thermofisher.com/de/de/home/materials-science/learning-center/applications/sem-tem-difference.html")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "SEM"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) is a type of electron microscopy where a focused beam of electrons scans the surface of an object. An image is created by detecting electrons reflected from the surface. Thus, SEM provides information on the surface and composition of the sample."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> (electron backscatter diffraction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "electron backscatter diffraction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "Electron Backscatter Diffraction (EBSD) is a SEM based technique for characterizing  material's local microstructure. EBSD provides an information about phases and their distribution in the material, grain structure, grain size, grain boundary, texture  (crystallographic orientation of individual grains), and local strain variation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "https://www.ebsd.com/ebsd-explained/what-is-ebsd")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "EBSD"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> (noes characteristic texture fibers)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> "noes characteristic texture fibers"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> "NOES characteristic texture fibers are the texure fibers which most commonly found in non-oriented electrical sheets. These fibers form preferred grain orientations in NOES, characterized by family of directions <uvw> oriented parallel to one of directions of a rolled sheet."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000038> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000040> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001930>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> (grain orientation)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> "grain orientation"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> "Grain orientation is an intensive quality of grains in material's microstructure, which describes the crystal orientation in respect to the external (sample's) reference frame. Grain orientation can be specified by either texture fibers or texture components. When several grains exhibit similar orientations, then the material exhibits a specific crystallographic texture."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> "Grain orientation is an intensive quality of grains in material's microstructure, which describes the crystallographic orientation in respect to the external (sample's) reference frame. Grain orientation can be a quality of an individual grain / crystallite or of a polycrystal, i.e., several grsins with similar crystallographic orientations.
Grain orientation can be specified by either texture fibers or texture components. When several grains exhibit similar orientations, then the material exhibits a specific crystallographic texture."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> "Cube orientation, λ-fiber orientation"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> (texture parameter Aθ)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> "texture parameter Aθ"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> "doi:10.1155/2008/173083")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> "Texture parameter is a intensive quality which quantifies crystallographic texture in materials. Texture parameter is defined as a minimun angle between the magnitization vector and the closest <100> direction in a crystal. Texture parameter can be derived from orientation distribution function (ODF) by integrating ODF f(g) multiplied by Aθ(g) over orientations dg."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> (direction averaged texture parameter A)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> "direction averaged texture parameter A"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> "doi:10.1155/2008/173083")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> "Direction averaged texture parameter A is a intensive quality which quantifies crystallographic texture in materials, which are utilized in applications where applied magnetic field is equally distributed in the rolling plane (RP) of the material. Direction averaged texture parameter A is derived from the texture parameter Aθ by integrating Aθ over dθ. For noriented electrical steels it can be simplified as (A0 + 2*A45 + A90) / 4, where A0, A45, and A90 are values of texture parameter Aθ for an applied magnetic field which encloses an angle of 0, 45, and 90 with the rolling direction, respectively."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> (texture factor)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> "texture factor"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> "Texture factor is an intensive quality used to quantify texture in materials. It is determined as sum of volume fractions of Goss and Cube texture components divided by the volume fraction of γ-fiber orientations."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> (transmission electron microscopy)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "transmission electron microscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "https://www.thermofisher.com/de/de/home/materials-science/learning-center/applications/sem-tem-difference.html")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "TEM"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) is a type of electron microscopy where a beam of electrons goes through a sample. An image is created by detecting electrons transmitted through the sample. Thus, TEM provides information on the crystal structure, morphology and stress state of the sample"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> (electron probe microanalysis)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> "electron probe microanalysis"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> "EPMA"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> "Electron probe microanalysis (EPMA) is a technique to non-destructively determine the chemical element composition of small volumes of solid materials. In EPMA an electron beam is focued on a single point of a surface of a sample. The energy of an electron beam is high enough for electrons to pentrate deeper in the sample causing excitation of characteristic x-rays. An x-ray spectrometer detects those characteristic x-rays providing information about materials chemical composition."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> (coercivity)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "A low H_c​ is desirable for soft magnetic materials like electrical steel, indicating easy magnetization and demagnetization"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "coercivity"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "Hc"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "coercive field strength"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "Coercivity is a magnetic property which is stimulated under an application of magnetic field. It describesthe value of the magnetic field strength H required to reduce the Magnetic Flux Density B back to zero after the material has been driven to the saturation of magnetic flux density B_sat."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> (magnetic induction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> "magnetic induction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> "Magnetic induction is a magnetic property stimulated by an applied extermal magnetic field H. It characterizes the response of magnetic domains within a material to the applied magnetic field, i.e., the alignment of the magnetic domains and the stregnth of an induced magnetic field in the material."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> (remanence)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "remanence"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "Br"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "remnant Induction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "Remanence is the magnetic induction B that remains in the material when the magnetic field strength H is reduced to zero."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> (saturation induction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "saturation induction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "Bsat"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "saturation magnetic flux density"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "Saturation induction is a magnetic property which is stimulated under an application of magnetic field. It characterizes the maximum induction B a material can achieve, i.e., the saturation induction is reached when it remains unchanged with increasing magnetic field strength H."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> (magnetic permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> "magnetic permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> "Magnetic permeability is a magnetic property that measures ability of a material to support the formation of a magnetic field within itself, and can be determined as the ratio between magnetic flux density / induction B and applied magnetic field strength H (μ=B/H)."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053> (magnetic power loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053> "magnetic power loss"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> (anomalous loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> "anomalous loss"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> (eddy current Loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> "eddy current Loss"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> (hysteresis loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> "hysteresis loss"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> (total magnetic power loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> "total magnetic power loss"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> (electrical resistivity)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> "electrical resistivity"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> "The electrical resistivity is an electrical property describing the ability of a material to oppose the flow of electric current. It is reciprocal to electric conductivity."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> (differential permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "Derivative dB/dH"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "differential permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "µ_d"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "Differential permeability is the instantaneous slope of the magnetization curve or hysteresis loop at any given point"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000060> (incremental permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000060> "incremental permeability"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> (initial permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "How easily the material magnetizes from rest"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "initial permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "µ_i"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "Initial permeability characterizes the slope of the tangent to the magnetization curve at the origin, i.e., H=0 and B=0. It represents the permeability in the weakest magnetic fields"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> (maximum permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "The maximum value of the normal permeability (the steepest line from the origin to the magnetization curve)."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "maximum permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "µ_max"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "Maximum permeability is the steepest part of the B-H curve, where the material most readily accepts field. it indicates the easiest magnetization point of the material,"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> (normal permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "A line from the origin to the loop tip"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "normal permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "μ_a"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "Normal permeabilty is the ratio of the peak magnetic induction B_peak to the peak magnetic field strength H_peak​ for a specific cycle"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000064> (reversible permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000064> "reversible permeability"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000064> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

